	<td bgcolor="#F7F7F7" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"> <b></b></font>
	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">I, too, was rather surprised at the support for clerical CC abilities on TDG. I think the three ideas SF mentioned are good and not too powerful.<br />
<br />
We must also consider what giving any CC abilities to clerics does to the other CC classes (bards, enchanters, necros somewhat). I feel confident in saying bards would still be wanted but it may dilute the enchanters desirability in groups, especially at the low end. Its would be the old "why get a enchanter when the cleric is 'good enough'?" This comes even more into play if we get a mezz type ability, however limited or inefficient.<br />
<br />
One down side is that additional CC abilities would have clerics doing the two most stressful jobs out there (CC and healing). If you thought burn out was bad now....<br />
<br />
So good idea, yes, but needs more discussion I think.</font></p>
	
	<p><p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">__________________<br>
Reorx Holybeard<br />
Level 65 (30 AA) Dwarven Cleric of Brell, Lord of Unrest, Bane of the Undead, Biter of Shins, Drinker of Ale (not nessecarily in that order)<br />
Tunare Server</font></p></p>
