<table bgcolor="#FFFFFF" width="95%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0"><tr><td width="10"><img width="10" height="1" src="images/space.gif" alt=""></td><td width="100%"><!-- spacer -->

<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" bgcolor=""  width="95%" align="center"><tr><td>
<table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="1" border="0"  width="100%">
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#F7F7F7" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post223679"></a>
	
	<font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>Arkhum</b></font><br>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">Cleric</font><br>
	<p>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">Registered: Apr 2003<br>
	Location: Central Texas<br>
	Posts: 12</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#F7F7F7" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"> <b></b></font>
	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><blockquote><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><hr><i>Originally posted by Shadowfrost </i><br />
<b>I accept that many clerics don't <i>want</i> changes to the priest classes and feel that things are fine as they are... I can understand that view, but I don't think that hoping to continue the status quo is realistic.<br />
</b><hr></blockquote><br />
<br />
I think that if enough clerics believe this it's going to be a self serving prophecy.  I'm sure I read somewhere that SOE thought healing was just fine the way it was (this was relatively recently, sometime after GoD anyway), but then I started seeing a big cleric push for "Let's get some upgrades cause they're going to nerf us anyway if we don't."  I think that push by clerics is going to be the impetus to get the ball rolling for major healing rebalancing.  But if that push wasn't there, I think the status quo could easily remain.  If you'd state that you don't want major healing changed, I really think SOE would listen.  We've been head and shoulders the top healer for 5 years.  Why would they change that now?<br />
<br />
Maybe a lot of you do really and truly want that but I personally don't.  I like my cleric the way he is, flaws and all.  I don't want enchanter powers, I don't want to become more  like a druid.  I don't want to see druids become more like me.  A couple minor upgrades for druids (and certainly for shaman) would be fine in my book but to allow them to heal all the content I can heal is asking for too much.<br />
<br />
Realistic or not, this is my stance on the matter.  I'd rather see my class left alone than watch it turn into something I never wanted to be.  I know a lot of posters here put a lot of thought into this rebalance effort and I do think it's admirable, but personally, I'd rather not see any of it happen.  Just my two copper, I'm gonna slink back into the bushes with the other lurkers now <img src="../ubb/biggrin.gif" border="0" alt=""></font></p>
	
	<p><p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">__________________<br>
Regards,<br />
Arkhum<br />
65 Archon</font></p></p>
	<p></p>
